Program: Great Lives
Title: Martha Gellhorn
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gj685
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 16 Jan 2007
Matthew Parris talks to editor of web gossip column Popbitch, Camilla Wright and biographer Caroline Moorhead about why the war reporter Martha Gellhorn, who covered the Spanish Civil War, WW2 and Vietnam, should be nominated for Great Lives status.